
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `aa-features-abi` baraye gereftan etela'at darbareye ABI (Application Binary Interface) az yek profile AppArmor estefade mishavad. Be zabane sade, in dastoor neshon midahad ke yek profile AppArmor az che ghabeliat-ha va vizhegi-haye ABI estefade mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `aa-features-abi <profile>` --> 🔍 Namayesh vizhegi-haye ABI baraye profile-ye moshakhas.
    🔹 `aa-features-abi --help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnama va tozihate bishtar darbareye dastoor.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/usr.bin.firefox

    🔹 Namayesh vizhegi-haye ABI profile Firefox.

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/sbin.dhcpd --help

    🔹 Namayesh rahnama va tozihate dastoor `aa-features-abi`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/usr.sbin.nscd

    🔹 Agar profile `nscd` az vizhegi-haye ABI estefade konad, list-e anha namayesh dade mishavad. Dar gheyr in soorat, hich chizi namayesh dade nemishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `aa-features-abi` command is used to retrieve information about the ABI (Application Binary Interface) features used by an AppArmor profile. Simply put, it shows which ABI features are used by a specific AppArmor profile.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `aa-features-abi <profile>` --> 🔍 Display ABI features for the specified profile.
    🔹 `aa-features-abi --help`  --> ❓ Display help and more information about the command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/usr.bin.firefox

    🔹 Display the ABI features of the Firefox profile.

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/sbin.dhcpd --help

    🔹 Display help and information about the `aa-features-abi` command.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ aa-features-abi /etc/apparmor.d/usr.sbin.nscd

    🔹 If the `nscd` profile utilizes ABI features, a list of those features will be displayed. Otherwise, nothing will be displayed.
